                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>I am glad you received the apocryphal New Testament I presume<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Dr Raphael</persName> is correct in stating that\n                                        the Publisher [?] was prosecuted<lb/> but I do not think it\n                                        could have been for this publication you will see<lb/> that\n                                        several of the books have been translated published in the\n                                        works<lb/> of learned men here. but I remember seeing in his\n                                        shop windows in<lb/> fleet street an atrocious caricature of\n                                        the almighty in which he was<lb/> depicted with all the\n                                        figurative descriptions used in the Bible <lb/> at the foot\n                                        \"Christians Here is your God as by Law established\"</p>\n                              <p>I believe few persons had the audacity to enter the shop purchase\n                                        it<lb/> I had not. I see the result of your interview with\n                                                  <persName>Mr Knit</persName> his<lb/> reply that\n                                        the synod had resolved to reply only to a Jewish\n                                        assembly<lb/> of [?] not to an individual is very\n                                        significant. however the ques<lb/>tion how my letter came to\n                                        the hands of the publisher of the asmonean<lb/> will soon be\n                                        solved for I see by the number for the week ending 20<lb/>\n                                        decr (which the publisher politely sent me) that my letter\n                                        was<lb/> sent to him by a Gentleman connected with the Synod\n                                        accompanied<lb/> by an answer which on account of the [?] of\n                                        the <sic>stile</sic> he did not<lb/> publish he proposed\n                                        doing up shortly with a running commentary</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">If the answer is signed by the writer requires any\n                                        other answer<lb/> than the commentary I shall perhaps take\n                                        notice of it, but not if it<lb/> is anonymous perhaps you\n                                        will say that my writings which you have<lb/> though worthy\n                                        of a place in your interesting periodical has also been<lb/>\n                                        anonymous by they have not been written to or at anybody but\n                                        your<lb/> self to any inquirers you could always supply the\n                                        name</p>\n                              <p>I read with much pleasure your review of <persName>Dr\n                                                  Raphel's</persName> lectures</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p32j68w7r/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
